  "instructions": [
    "In a large pot, heat the vegetable oil over medium heat.",
    "Add the chopped onion, carrots, and celery; cook until tender, about 5 minutes.",
    "Add the turkey necks and cook for 5 minutes, browning on all sides.",
    "Add the beet juice, chicken broth, red wine vinegar, sugar, salt, and black pepper; bring to a boil.",
    "Reduce heat to low and simmer for 1 hour, or until the turkey necks are tender.",
    "Remove the turkey necks from the pot and let cool.",
    "Once cooled, remove the meat from the bones and shred; return the meat to the pot.",
    "Stir in chopped fresh dill; serve the borscht warm, garnished with additional dill if desired."
